The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Model code violated
                                                                                                               Model code violated
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT      
	Patna, March 9: The administration has lodged a case of violation of model code of conduct against four Bihar MPs, including murder convict and RJDs Madhepura MP Pappu Yadav, and his MP wife, Ranjita Ranjan.         
	Others facing election code violation cases are BJP national spokesman and Rajya Sabha MP Rajiv Pratap Rudi and RJD Patna MP Ramkripal Yadav.        
	Sources in the state election office revealed that the Chapra police had lodged a case against Rajiv Pratap Rudi for holding a news meet at the government-owned Circuit House at Chapra (Saran) and meeting party workers there on March 4.        
	Madhepura MP Pappu Yadav, who was recently released on bail, and his wife Ranjita Ranjan, an LJP MP from Saharsa, are accused of violating code of conduct by using more than stipulated number of vehicles for their rally at Khajanchihat, Purnea on March 7.         
	Purnea SDO A.D. Thakre said: The MPs were allowed five vehicles, but they used more.        
	Masauri (Patna) block development officer Chandan Kumar said Patna MP Ramkripal Yadav was found prima facie guilty of violating the code by holding a public function without permission at Kharaunj village three days ago.                                                                                                                                                                            
